  "instructions": [
    "Marinate the oxtail in a mixture of soy sauce, brown sugar, fish sauce, lemon juice, and pepper for at least an hour.",
    "Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Sauté garlic and green onions until fragrant.",
    "Add marinated oxtail to the pan, reducing to low-medium heat. Cook until the oxtail is tender and nicely caramelized on all sides.",
    "Stir in vegetable stock and simmer for an additional 10 minutes to thicken the sauce.",
    "Serve hot with steamed vegetables or rice."
